Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 413
An Act Regarding Disclosure by Sellers of Residential Real Property
of Notices of Shoreland Zoning Ordinance Violations
Reference to the Committee on Housing and Economic Development suggested and
ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative DUCHARME of Madison.
Cosponsored by Representatives: ARATA of New Gloucester, BLIER of Buxton, CRAY of
Palmyra, POIRIER of Skowhegan, Senator: BERNARD of Aroostook.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 33 MRSA §173, sub-§8, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 602, §5 and reallocated
3 by RR 2023, c. 2, Pt. A, §52, is amended to read:
4 8. Notice of violation. Detailed information on an actual or alleged violation of a
5 shoreland zoning ordinance adopted pursuant to Title 38, chapter 3, subchapter 1, article
6 2‑B, including those that were state-imposed, imposed on and applicable to the property.
7 SUMMARY
88 Under current law, a seller of residential real property must provide to a purchaser a
99 property disclosure statement that includes, among other things, information regarding
1100 actual or alleged violations of shoreland zoning ordinances imposed on and applicable to
1111 the property. This bill removes the reference in that law to alleged shoreland zoning
1122 violations but otherwise maintains the disclosure requirement for actual shoreland zoning
1133 violations.
Page 1 - 132LR0917(01)
